{
  "text": "Ap-intersection vector bundle on X may be defined as an actual vector bundle on IpX. Using simply connected surgery [CITATION_1] , one can show that there are infinitely many distinct 7-dimensional pseudomanifolds X, whose tangent bundle elements in the KO-theory KO(X \u2212Sing) of their nonsingular parts do not lift to KO(X), but do lift to KO(InX), wheren is the upper middle perversity. So this framework allows one to formulate the requirement that a pseudomanifold have ap-intersection tangent bundle. In the isolated singularity case, the obstruction to lifting to KO(InX) lies in the KO-theory of the truncated link, which is roughly half as big as the KO-theory of the link itself.",
  "citation_candidates": [
